    num_likes: 57200,
    num_views: 989400,
    videoUrl: UGC(11),
    thumbnail: WI(1),
    textOverlay: "My therapist said: 'Boundaries aren't walls. They're gates. You decide who gets in and when.'\n\nThat changed everything for me. I used to think setting boundaries meant being mean. It doesn't. It means being clear.\n\n'I can't take calls after 7pm' isn't rude. It's self-preservation.\n'I need a day to think about that' isn't weak. It's wise.\n'I love you but I can't help you with this' isn't selfish. It's honest.\n\nThe hardest boundary I ever set was with my own mother. I told her she couldn't comment on my weight anymore. She cried. I almost caved. But 6 months later, our relationship is better than it's been in 20 years.\n\nBoundaries feel terrible at first because we're used to people-pleasing. But the discomfort of setting a boundary lasts a moment. The resentment of not setting one lasts years.",
