    textOverlay: "He was manipulative, gaslighting, and emotionally unavailable. But 2 years later, I realize he accidentally taught me everything I needed to know about myself.\n\nHe taught me that I was a people pleaser. Because I bent myself into a pretzel trying to make him happy while completely ignoring my own needs.\n\nHe taught me my attachment style. I was anxious-attached, and that's WHY I was drawn to someone avoidant.\n\nHe taught me that love isn't supposed to feel like anxiety. The butterflies I thought were excitement? That was my nervous system in fight-or-flight.\n\nHe taught me what I actually want. Because now I have a crystal clear list of non-negotiables.\n\nHe taught me that I'm stronger than I thought. Because I survived it. And I'm thriving.\n\nI'm not thanking him. I'm thanking myself for choosing to grow from it instead of letting it break me.\n\nHealing isn't linear but it IS happening.",
