    textOverlay: "Motivation is a scam. There, I said it.\n\nFor years I waited to 'feel motivated' before doing anything. Guess what? I wasted years. Because motivation is an emotion, and emotions are unreliable.\n\nWhat actually works: systems.\n\nI don't wait to feel like going to the gym. My gym bag is in my car. I drive there after work automatically. The decision was made on Sunday.\n\nI don't wait to feel like writing content. I sit down at 6am every day with my coffee. Some days the writing is garbage. But I ship it anyway.\n\nI don't wait to feel like making sales calls. I block 10-11am every day. When the calendar says call, I call.\n\nDiscipline > motivation. Every single time.\n\nThe people you admire aren't more motivated than you. They just built systems that remove the need for motivation.\n\nStop watching motivational videos and start building your system. Today.",
