    textOverlay: "Short answer: yes. Long answer: it's complicated.\n\nI was stuck at $8k/month for 6 months. Tried everything. New strategies, new platforms, new offers. Nothing worked. So I invested $10k in a coach. Terrifying.\n\nWhat she did in the first session: told me I had too many offers. I was selling 7 different things. She made me pick ONE and go all in.\n\nMonth 1: Revenue dropped to $5k. I panicked.\nMonth 2: $9k. Okay, back to normal.\nMonth 3: $16k. Wait what?\nMonth 4: $23k. I literally screamed.\n\nWhat she really did was give me clarity and accountability. I already knew what to do — I just needed someone to hold me to it and stop me from shiny-object-syndroming.\n\nWas it worth $10k? I made an extra $80k in the 6 months after. So mathematically, 8x ROI.\n\nBut here's my honest take: most coaches aren't worth it. Ask for client results. Talk to their students. If they can't show receipts, run.",
