    textOverlay: "Last month my Shopify store did $52,000 in revenue. Everyone congratulated me. Here's the reality:\n\nCOGS (product cost): $15,600 (30%)\nShipping: $5,200 (10%)\nAd spend: $13,000 (25%)\nShopify + apps: $380\nReturns/refunds: $2,600 (5%)\nVA + customer service: $1,600\nPackaging: $1,040\nTransaction fees: $1,560\n\nTotal expenses: $40,980\nActual profit: $11,020\n\nThat's a 21% profit margin. On a '$52k month.'\n\nAnd that doesn't include my time. If I paid myself hourly for the 50 hours I worked, that's $220/hour. Not bad. But it's not the '$52k month' everyone sees on the screenshot.\n\nRevenue is vanity. Profit is sanity. Cash flow is reality.\n\nNext time someone flexes their revenue, ask about their margins. The silence will tell you everything.",
