    textOverlay: "I moved into my own apartment at 24. No roommates. No partner. Just me and my thoughts. It was the most important thing I've ever done.\n\nYou learn what you actually like to eat when nobody's watching. (Turns out I love cooking elaborate meals for one.)\n\nYou learn how you handle loneliness. The first month, the silence was deafening. By month 3, I craved it.\n\nYou learn your real routine — not the one you perform for others. I discovered I'm a morning person who likes to dance while cleaning.\n\nYou learn to fix things. YouTube taught me how to unclog a drain, hang shelves, and reset a circuit breaker.\n\nYou learn that you're genuinely good company. This was the biggest gift.\n\nLiving alone isn't lonely. It's the most intimate relationship you'll ever have — with yourself. And you need that foundation before you can truly share your space with someone else.",
