    num_likes: 16730,
    num_views: 289400,
    videoUrl: V(4),
    thumbnail: WI(3),
    textOverlay: "Hot take: your morning routine is not why you're successful or unsuccessful. And I'm tired of the internet pretending it is.\n\nYou don't need to wake up at 4:30am. You don't need a cold plunge. You don't need to journal, meditate, AND do breathwork before the sun rises.\n\nYou know what you need? To do the hard thing you've been avoiding.\n\nI know people who wake up at 5am, do their entire 'optimal morning routine,' and then spend 8 hours doing busy work. I also know people who roll out of bed at 9, drink coffee, and build empires by noon.\n\nThe difference isn't the routine. It's the execution.\n\nAre you doing deep work or shallow work? Are you creating or consuming? Are you moving the needle or just moving?\n\nStop optimizing the container and start optimizing the content. Your morning routine is the appetizer. Your actual work is the main course.\n\nNobody became a millionaire because of their morning routine. They became one because they did things other people weren't willing to do.",
