    textOverlay: "3 years ago I was at my lowest. Breakup. Lost my job. Moved back in with my parents at 27. I couldn't get out of bed most days.\n\nMy friend dragged me to the gym. I didn't want to go. I had zero energy. I could barely bench the empty bar.\n\nBut something happened. For that one hour, my brain went quiet. No overthinking. No spiraling. Just me vs. the weight.\n\nI went back the next day. And the next. And the next.\n\nThe weights got heavier. My body changed. But more importantly, my mind changed. I started to feel CAPABLE again. If I could add 10 pounds to my squat, maybe I could rebuild my life too.\n\n6 months later I was 30 lbs of muscle heavier, in a new apartment, with a new job. The gym didn't just give me a physique. It gave me proof that I could do hard things.\n\nTo anyone reading this in their dark place: just show up. You don't need a plan. You don't need motivation. You just need to walk through the door.\n\nThe bar is always there. And it never judges you.",
