    num_views: 234200,
    videoUrl: V(6),
    thumbnail: WI(5),
    textOverlay: "1. 'Atomic Habits' by James Clear — I know everyone recommends this. But there's a reason. The 1% better every day concept literally rewired how I approach everything.\n\n2. 'The Psychology of Money' by Morgan Housel — changed my relationship with money. Wealth isn't what you earn. It's what you DON'T spend.\n\n3. 'Attached' by Amir Levine — understanding attachment theory explained every failed relationship I've ever had. Should be required reading.\n\n4. 'Buy Back Your Time' by Dan Martell — as an entrepreneur, this book showed me I was the bottleneck. Delegation isn't lazy. It's leverage.\n\n5. '$100M Offers' by Alex Hormozi — if you sell anything, this book pays for itself 1000x. Your offer is the problem, not your marketing.\n\nMy reading system: 30 minutes every morning before my phone. Kindle so I can highlight. Review highlights weekly.\n\nBooks are the cheapest mentorship in the world. A $15 book contains someone's entire life of learning.",
