    videoUrl: UGC(44),
    thumbnail: WI(0),
    textOverlay: "Everyone says dating gets worse after 30. I completely disagree. Here's why it's actually better:\n\nYou know yourself. You're not trying to figure out who you are while simultaneously trying to figure out a relationship. You KNOW your dealbreakers.\n\nYou've been through stuff. Heartbreak, therapy, growth. You bring a more healed version of yourself to the table.\n\nYou have less time to waste. So you cut through the BS faster. 'What are you looking for?' isn't scary anymore. It's efficient.\n\nThe people you meet are more intentional. They're not dating for entertainment. They're dating because they actually want a partner.\n\nYou're more comfortable being alone. Which means you choose people for the right reasons — not because you're scared of being single.\n\nYes, the pool is smaller. But the quality? It's so much higher. I'd rather have 5 great options than 50 mediocre ones.\n\n30s dating: fewer games, more honesty, better connection. Don't let the internet scare you.",
