    tags: ["B2B SaaS/Platform", "Productivity"],
    num_likes: 15890,
    num_views: 274500,
    videoUrl: V(0),
    thumbnail: WI(1),
    textOverlay: "I run a $30k/month business in 15 hours per week. Here's the automation stack:\n\nLead generation: LinkedIn content -> link in bio -> landing page -> email sequence. All automated after I post.\n\nOnboarding: Client signs contract -> Stripe auto-charges -> Notion template auto-creates -> welcome email sends -> Calendly link delivered. Zero manual steps.\n\nContent: I batch-create one month of content in 2 days. Scheduled through Buffer. Repurposed with Repurpose.io across 4 platforms.\n\nClient delivery: SOPs in Loom. Templates in Notion. Slack channel auto-created. 80% of questions answered by a knowledge base.\n\nFinance: QuickBooks syncs with Stripe. Invoices auto-generate. Tax estimates quarterly via my accountant's portal.\n\nThe key insight: every time you do something more than twice, document it and automate it. Your future self will thank you.\n\nTime invested to build this: ~200 hours over 6 months. Time saved per year: ~1,500 hours. That math changed my life.",
