    num_views: 342700,
    videoUrl: UGC(45),
    thumbnail: WI(2),
    textOverlay: "My dad worked 60-hour weeks for 35 years. Never complained. Never missed a payment. Gave us everything.\n\nLast Thanksgiving, we were sitting on the porch, and I asked him: 'Dad, if you could do it all over, what would you change?'\n\nHe was quiet for a long time. Then he said: 'I would have been there more. I thought providing was the same as being present. It's not.'\n\nThat broke me.\n\nHe continued: 'I missed your first steps because I was in a meeting. I missed your school play because I was closing a deal. I missed a hundred small moments because I thought the big moments would make up for it.'\n\nI asked him what he'd tell young men today. He said: 'The job will replace you in two weeks. Your family never will. Act accordingly.'\n\nI think about this conversation every single day. I've restructured my entire life around it. Money matters. But time with the people you love matters infinitely more.\n\nDad, if you're reading this: you were enough. You always were.",
